e="preserve">Harold Janeway (February 3, 1936 – August 20, 2020) was an American politician and businessman. He was a Democratic member of the New Hampshire Senate, representing the 7th District from 2006 to 2010. He was born in Glen Cove, New York.
Janeway died of prostate cancer on August 20, 2020, in Webster, New Hampshire at the age of 84.
